meanings.definition: To gnaw or chew through completely.
meanings.sent1: The hungry squirrel outgnawned the nut to get to the tasty center.
meanings.sent2: The beaver outgnawned the log to build its dam.
meanings.sent3: The determined rabbit outgnawned the carrot to reach the sweet core.
meanings.sent4: The termite outgnawned the wooden structure, leaving it weak and fragile.
meanings.sent5: The mouse outgnawned the cheese, leaving behind a perfect circle.

meanings.definition: To surpass in gnawing or chewing.
meanings.sent1: The hungry rat outgnawned all the other rodents to finish the food first.
meanings.sent2: The eager puppy outgnawned its siblings to get the biggest bone.
meanings.sent3: The competitive squirrels outgnawned each other to gather the most acorns.
meanings.sent4: The diligent caterpillar outgnawned its peers to become the first butterfly.
meanings.sent5: The persistent beaver outgnawned the competition to claim the best spot for its dam.
